 The following sample displays the caller DN for a call in the 
 CSTADelivered event fired on the VDN "8542".

 //C# Sample:

	//The event handler for the "VDNCallChanged" event.
	private void asxmlvdn1_VDNCallChanged(object sender, AgileSoftware.Developer.VDN.VDNCallChangedEventArgs arg)
	{
		//VDN 8542 only.
		if (arg.VDNNumber != "8542") return;

		//Captures the "CSTADelivered" type call event.
		if (arg.CallEvent.CallEventType == AgileSoftware.Developer.Device.enCallEventType.CSTADelivered)
		{
			AgileSoftware.Developer.CSTA.CSTADeliveredEventArgs _EventInfo = (AgileSoftware.Developer.CSTA.CSTADeliveredEventArgs)arg.CallEvent.EventInfo;

			Console.WriteLine("CSTADelivered event on VDN 8542: Caller DN = {0}", _EventInfo.CallingDevice.ID);
		}
	}

	'VB Sampe:

	Private Sub Asxmlvdn1_VDNCallChanged(ByVal sender As System.Object, ByVal arg As AgileSoftware.Developer.VDN.VDNCallChangedEventArgs) Handles Asxmlvdn1.VDNCallChanged

		'Captures the "CSTADelivered" type call event on VDN 8542.
		If arg.CallEvent.CallEventType = AgileSoftware.Developer.Device.enCallEventType.CSTADelivered And arg.VDNNumber = "8542" Then

			Dim EventInfo As AgileSoftware.Developer.CSTA.CSTADeliveredEventArgs = CType(arg.CallEvent.EventInfo, AgileSoftware.Developer.CSTA.CSTADeliveredEventArgs)

			Console.WriteLine("CSTADelivered event on VDN 8542: Caller DN = {0}", EventInfo.CallingDevice.ID)
		End If
	End Sub

member.summary:
A state in which call progression is suspended or made inactive 
while awaiting some form of action. For exmple a call is queued at a distribution mechanism, 
waiting for an agent to become available. (Queue = 5)

A state in which call progression is suspended or made inactive 
while awaiting some form of action. For exmple a call is queued at a distribution mechanism, 
waiting for an agent to become available. (Queue = 5)

The format of the socket message pack: 
0,1: 00(TCP No Soap), 01 (SOAP); 
2,3: Message Body Length, Max: 0xFFFF ; 
4->: Message Body

member.remarks:
The format of the socket message pack: 
0,1: TCP No Soap: 00; Tcp with SOAP: 01; 
2,3: Message Body Length, Max: 0xFFFF ; 
4->: TCP No Soap: 4,5,6,7 (InvokeID) 8-> (XML Message body; 
4->: TCP with Soap: 4-> XML Message body.

CSTATCPMsgReturn event is fired with the InvokeID and XMLMsg properties 
after the ValidateMsgPack method is called and a compelet message is identified.

